Key Match Events: Pakistan win by three wickets with seven balls to spare
Ireland slump to 32-6 but manage to post 106-9
Shaheen Afridi bowled superbly at the top of Ireland's innings, but I didn't see him winning it with the bat if I'm honest.
Post-Match Reflections: Pakistan captain Babar Azam: ‘When we started with the bowling, we got ahead. In the batting, we didn’t finish well but when you have back-to-back wickets, you have to go to the end with the tailenders.'
Ireland captain Paul Stirling: 'We played in patches. We didn't start the day terribly well and they put pressure on us early on. I think that was the difference in the end.'
Miscellaneous Highlights: Both sides had already been eliminated from Super 8s contention
Others: This was the 100th meeting between the two teams
